animals are tension tamers too events at stanford animals are tension tamers too facebook twitter email print add to calendar americans love their pets why is that the answer is not complicated the relationships between domesticated animals and humans are less stressful than human relationships what's not to love about a companion who does not make judgments criticize care what you wear or how you look or how much money you make a pet's simple nonjudgmental attention can coax you from the deepest preoccupation into the present moment and help you shift perspective in this class we will review the growing body of research supporting the positive impact that pets can have on blood pressure stress reaction loneliness and depression learn tips on how to allow your pet to serve as your tension tamer explore ways to receive the stress reducing benefits of animals without actually owning a pet instructor janada clark ma health educator and stanford hip and worklife instructor when friday january 27 2012 12 00 pm approximate duration of 1.0 hour s where li ka shing learning ctr rm 306 map audience general public faculty staff alumni friends members tags class health wellness sponsor health improvement program contact 650 721 6003 ausserer stanford edu admission register at hip stanford edu fee $25.00 stap ea funds yes class code attt 01 permalink http events stanford edu events 302 30221 more info last modified december 16 2011
